## Description

Implement a feature to save user-defined data snapshots, allowing users to specify the snapshot category and snapshot filename, and save the serialized data content into the corresponding snapshot file. The system uses the `writeFileSync` API from the `fs` module to perform file writing operations. It constructs the final file path by joining the `/tmp/resources` directory with the user-provided category and filename using `path.join`. Users can control the category and filename parameters to facilitate categorized storage of temporary data snapshots according to different scenarios.

